  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Prompt**\n\nOkay, I\'m diving in! I\'ve started by meticulously dissecting the user\'s prompt. I\'m focusing on identifying the core requirements for the web application based on the HTML, design elements, CSS, images and components that have been specified.\n\n\n**Defining Core App Elements**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the essential components based on the user\'s detailed specification for the \"FYC 2026\" app. The focus is on the title, theme (\"Timeless Truth for a Changing World\" tied to Hebrews 13:8), and core screens. I\'m taking special note of the branding guidelines, the \"Diocese of Canada, Malankara Orthodox Syrian Church\" details and the inclusion of the seal image, alongside the structure for the home screen and its countdown function.\n\n\n**Outlining Application Features**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the specifics for the Home screen. This includes a dynamic countdown timer for the conference start, the \"Welcome Home\" section with its action cards linking to schedule and songs, and a clear presentation of date, location (Georgian College, Barrie, Ontario), and a map component or detailed view. Finally, I\'ve outlined the Keynote Speakers section with their images and details, including Rev. Fr. Dr. Timothy Thomas and Very. Rev. Dr. Johns Abraham.\n\n\n**Expanding Speaker Section**\n\nI\'ve added Rev. Fr. Dr. Abraham George\'s details and image to the Keynote Speakers section. The scripture footer, \"Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today and forever,\" is now included. I\'m moving on to defining the Schedule and Songs screens.\n\n\n**Defining Song and Map Features**\n\nI\'m now outlining a robust song library for the FYC 2026 app, making it searchable and filterable, including Malayalam, English, and transliterated versions with a lyrics modal. I\'m prioritizing the development of a polished, interactive map or campus layout guide for Georgian College in Barrie, Ontario, potentially using an iframe and styled directions, or an interactive campus layout finder. I\'m also planning for side navigation with interactive overlays and local data persistence.\n\n\n**Incorporating Brand Colors**\n\nI\'m now integrating the user\'s specified color palette: dark blue (`#000a1e`, `#002147`) and ecclesiastical gold (`#fed65b`, `#735c00`). I\'m planning to implement these as custom Tailwind classes or CSS styles. My review of available skills is completed. I\'m focusing on adhering to the user\'s specific request to build an app that matches provided screens, so I\'ll avoid unrequested skill use.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Core Skills**\n\nI\'ve decided to lean into simplicity. I\'ve reevaluated potential skill integrations like `image-generation` and `google-maps-platform`. While initially considered, I\'m now opting for a straightforward approach, directly leveraging the provided image hotlinks from the HTML, and implementing an elegant map display instead of complex routing. My priority is to keep the app focused on the core conference content and location.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 306398300
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
