  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Celebrating Flawless Compile**\n\nI\'m thrilled! The compile was flawless on the initial attempt \342\200\223 a testament to pristine engineering. Now, my focus shifts towards summarizing this success and creating a stunning presentation. I\'ll need to ensure the presentation adheres precisely to formatting guidelines.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Framework**\n\nI\'m currently refining the visual styling based on the plan. I\'m leveraging a dark ecclesiastical theme with gold accents for a sense of solemnity, alongside a spacious layout. I\'ve designed the countdown module to be responsive and dynamically calculates real-time remaining values. The brand theme focuses on maintaining a structured visual hierarchy.\n\n\n**Constructing Comprehensive Features**\n\nI\'ve just finished creating a comprehensive, interactive multi-day schedule with categorized sessions and query searching. It also includes collapsible details with speaker indices, personalized bookmarking, and private journal drafts with auto-save capabilities. Furthermore, I engineered a searchable hymnal collection with parallel English/Malayalam layouts, font size controls, and a custom Web Audio pitch chime helper. I\'m also modeling Georgian College campus maps and transit guides with SVG visual layouts.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have built a fully interactive, responsive mobile-first web application for the **Diocese of Canada Family & Youth Conference 2026**, matching the provided visual guidelines and the liturgical tone of the Malankara Orthodox Syrian Church.\n\nHere is a summary of the design choices and high-level functional modules implemented:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual Identity & Traditional Design\n* **Ecclat Gold & Navy Theme**: Designed with a high-contrast palette consisting of deep primary navy backgrounds, clean white surface layers, and ecclesiastical gold accents to evoke visual authority, respect, and church inheritance.\n* **Classical Typography Pairings**: Implemented **Noto Serif** for display headings to convey traditional gravity, and **Work Sans** as the clean, highly legible workhorse for schedule tables, lists, and form labels.\n* **Spacious Structural Layouts**: Employed generous spacing and subtle container outlines to allow the holy scripture sections and imagery elements to breathe naturally.\n\n### \342\217\261\357\270\217 Core Functional & Interactive Modules\n\n1. **Active Countdown Tracker**:\n   * Features a live dynamic ticker counting down days, hours, minutes, and seconds from the user\'s current local timezone to the conference gate opening on July 2, 2026.\n\n2. **Interactive Liturgical & Plenary Schedule**:\n   * Organized a comprehensive three-day agenda with custom category badges (*Liturgy*, *Workshops*, *Social*, *Youth assemblies*).\n   * Developed real-time keyword search and category dropdown filters.\n   * Built expandable session rows revealing speaker profiles, direct clergyman panel question submissions, star bookmarking to compile a personalized timetable, and private note-taking sheets that automatically persist in your local browser cache.\n\n3. **Tradition Chants & Hymnals Library**:\n   * Configured a sacred song interface holding English translations and transliterated Malayalam lyrics side-by-side.\n   * Added dynamic font size controllers (step-magnificate from 12px to 24px) for older delegates and children.\n   * Engineered an offline-capable **melody pitch stabilizer** using the native *HTML5 Web Audio API* to synthesize and play G-major clean pentatonic chord frequencies simulating traditional cathedral flutes.\n\n4. **Georgian College Directions & Interactive Map**:\n   * Constructed an interactive SVG campus floor layout plotting dorm check-ins, assembly auditoriums, and prayer chapels with responsive instructions.\n   * Added a driving directions analyzer detailing highways exits, estimated travel periods, and parking regulations for major starting cities (*Toronto*, *Ottawa*, *Montreal*), as well as custom address entries.\n   * Mapped localized listings for accommodations, dining options, and beachfront scenic spots near the Barrie Campus.\n\n5. **Pass Ticket Registration Desk**:\n   * Developed an elegant conference booking sheet securing seats for parallel workshops.\n   * Outputs a physical-style high-contrast digital ticket pass displaying the delegate\'s custom receipt timestamp, registered workshops, and an offline check-in QR code block ready to scan at the welcoming desk.\n\n6. **Youth Connect Wall**:\n   * Provided a communal dialogue post board where students and family delegates can post greetings, select traditional icons, and pair them with customized canvas background styles.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 297944938
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
