    thinking: "**Clarifying Vite Server Behaviour**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how Vite servers handle file serving. It seems if a `public` directory exists, that takes precedence. Otherwise, it defaults to the root, as long as the references in `index.html` are correct, especially for dynamic imports. This observation led me to reconsider where to place certain assets.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create a `/public` directory and place the `manifest.webmanifest` and a lightweight caching Service Worker `sw.js` inside it. In Vite, any file placed in `/public` is automatically served at the root `/` and bundled directly into the build output `dist/` without compilation. This ensures the files are accessible on Android devices exactly where the browser expects them."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 127539962
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
